constituent: cat, pack of wild dogs, seedlings, flowers, rice field, brains
heisigStory: Knowing how much dogs love to chase cats, picture a pack of wild dogs planting "cat-seedlings," watering them, and fertilizing them until they can be harvested as a crop of cats for them to chase and torment. If you begin from the key word and think of a "crop of cats," you will not confuse this story with the apparently similar story of two frames ago.
koohiiStory1: The cat hid in the FLOWERS of the FIELD from the WILD DOGs.
koohiiStory2: Dawgs always wanna put their seedlings in pussies.
